The area outside Capital One Arena is clogged with people hoping to make it into the venue now hosting the presidential parade due to the 22-degree weather.
It’s a zoo — with sidewalks so crowded it’s hard to move and vendors hawking their Trump merchandise as flamboyantly as they can.
“Daddy’s home!” one seller is yelling from a corner as people stream past. He is alternating between that and shouting profane slogans from his T-shirts. Elsewhere, a handful of Trump supporters from New Jersey are dressed as the Founding Fathers.
